, Msb, * K,) with which ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAgiyapN", "text_ar": "رَاغِيَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is syn. [either as an inf. n. or as a simple subst.]; (JK;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He grumbled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uttered a grumbling cry;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Daj~a", "text_ar": "ضَجَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uttered a cry,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and grumbled;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Saw~ata faDaj~a", "text_ar": "صَوَّتَ فَضَجَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "she uttered a cry"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[&c.]: (Msb:) so camels are wont to do when the loads are lifted upon them; and youthful camels do so much: (TA:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rugaA='N", "text_ar": "رُغَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cry"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "crying"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grumbling,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of gurgling growl,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (S, Msb) of the camel [when he is being laden, and on some other occasions of discontent], (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1115}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or of animals having the kind of foot called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuf~", "text_ar": "خُفّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) also of the bird called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rag~aA='N", "text_ar": "رَغَّا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[&c.]. (TA.) It is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kafaY birugaAy^ihaA munaAdiyFA", "text_ar": "كَفَى بِرُغَايِهَا مُنَادِيًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Her grumbling cry suffices as a caller"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] i. e., the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rugaA='", "text_ar": "رُغَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of his camel serves instead of his calling in presenting himself for entertainment as a guest: (S:) A'Obeyd says that it is well known to the Arabs as relating to the accomplishment of an object of want before the asking for it: and it is applied also to the case of a man whose aid is wanted and who does not come to thee; excusing himself by saying that he did not know: and to the case of one who stands at a man's door, and to whom it is said, “ Send him who shall ask permission for thee [to go in]; ” whereupon he replies, “ His knowledge of my standing at his door suffices for asking permission for me: if he pleased, he would grant me permission. ” (Meyd. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 328—9.]) And in another prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albakori", "text_ar": "البَكْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAnato Ealayohimo karaAgiyapi", "text_ar": "كَانَتْ عَلَيْهِمْ كَرَاغِيَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (JK, Meyd,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~aqobi", "text_ar": "السَّقْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There befell them the like of the grumbling cry of the young camel,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meaning, the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rugaA='", "text_ar": "رُغَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the young camel of Thamood [which preceded the destruction of those who heard it]: the prov. relates to the auguring evil from a thing. (Meyd. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 327.]) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ragaA", "text_ar": "رَغَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said of a boy, or child, means (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He wept most violently."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b3-  [It is also, app., said of a man, as meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He shouted:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he spoke with a loud voice."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(See 6, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rag~aA='N", "text_ar": "رَغَّا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)]       -A2-  See also 2.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Mgh", "K", "Msb", "TA", "JK", "Meyd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}